					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Toni Morrison</h4>
												<p>Toni Morrison wrote eleven novels, from <em>The Bluest Eye</em> (1970) to <em>God Help the Child</em> (2015), and she received the National Book Critics Circle Award and the Pulitzer Prize. In 1993, she was awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature. She died in 2019 at the age of 88.</p>
